text: We've been driving back and forth from my parents a lot this past week to be with family and to be there with my dad. As we were driving down to their house yesterday the views were breathtaking. I took a video of the first one I saw, but after saw many more during the drive. As we would turn a corner, the sunset behind the snow capped mountains looked angelic. Then around the lake the reflections were magnificent. Each view getting more and more beautiful. I knew that videos wouldn't do them justice. A few minutes later (right before we arrived at my parents), my brother JC called and said Dad had made the transition. I can't help but wonder if this was a little tender mercy, Gods way of telling me just how wonderful eternity will be. This is just the beginning. Life with my dad was incredibly beautiful, I don't have words to describe how grateful I am to be his daughter. I also know there is so much more to come. Until we meet again, Daddy. I will be missing you everyday.üïäÔ∏è‚ù§Ô∏è
